Stir together the honey, salt, milk, coconut milk, and melted butter. Add the corn, cover, and refrigerate overnight. Preheat a charcoal grill for medium heat. Remove corn from marinade and place each one on a skewer. Grill for 10 to 15 minutes until partially charred, baste occasionally with the coconut marinade as you grill. Serve with 1 tablespoon of butter per ear.